column5: I was able to locate customer number and order number.  I was able to call and request invoice emailed.
Ordering from Scholastic is very easy. I like the free books because I always use this promo to buy books for the class.

I am a grandparent, and I didn't like that you can't check out as a guest.  I don't know if my creating an account affects if his parents can still create an account.  I really like the book clubs, and the book fairs.  Thank you.
Have so many books to choose from my son absolutely loves these!
Easy to navigate and great selections
The experience with Scholastic Book Clubs has been very good!
Site is easy to use. Love that it links to PayPal, so convenient and efficient.
Love that scholastic books helps me grow my classroom library for my students!
Grew up ordering from SCHOLASTIC's in middle school and love the fact I can do the same for my kids.
easy to enter online orders. Great service and prices are fair.
Thanks for being such an easy company fpr teachers to work with!
Everything went very smoothly no problems at all.
We love all the different bundled books
I find the website easy to navigate
The website is excellent.   User Friendly
Using the Online ordering system is so much easier! I love it.
Very easy to find what I needed and check out
This site was very user friendly!
I really enjoy these books, there is a wide variety and my kids always have several that they want to get. Also very good deals on books!
I had a question about bonus points, and I asked the online service, so very helpful and quick to answer.
They were very helpful on the live chat.  Ed put a replacement order in for me.
We always enjoy looking through the scholastic  book orders to choose our books
I like how everything is organized by student name.  Quick and easy to put in my order.
I've been a very satisfied long-time (over 20 years) customer and will continue to encourage my students to buy books from Scholastic.  Thank you.
Thank you so much, I am excited to have the opportunity to be part of the scholastic book club.
Love the website. Very easy to use!
Was shopping around.  Still not done.  Might place an order yet.
Scholastic is always consistent with service.

I love the diversity Scholastic offers. As a parent who raises children to be inclusive and kind to everyone, I appreciate that Scholastic has a wide range of book options that every child can find themselves in.
Great site! Very easy to use and check out. Will definitely return to order more.

We appreciate Scholastic Book Clubs very much!  You help us place books in students' hands, and you help fund and stock our Classroom Library.  You help create a huge part of our classroom community's core by helping us further our love and enjoyment of literacy.
Great that it remembered my info so that I was able to go, order, and pay so quickly
We love your books that you provide to kids!
I enjoy shopping for books for my child and it helps support the school my child attends.
My family loves the scholastic books program! Thank you for providing a variety of books that are exciting and engaging. An extra perk-- many of them are A.R. books!
Not an easy site to navigate and actually find what you want and I’m very tech savvy. Always takes a long time to get an order together. Prices are great though.
Great support for teachers and parents.
I have no points even though I  ordered Scholastic News and Science Spin for my second and third grade students.
It has been a great 26 years of ordering through Scholastic Book Clubs.
easy to maneuver, find items, and order
I love the idea that schools can provide books monthly for the students.

I've loved Scholastic Book Clubs since I was a kid longingly looking through the fliers for books to purchase. Now that I'm a parent,  I can buy reading level-appropriate books for my kids to my, er, THEIR hearts' content!
Very happy with book selection and the set up of the website.  Very user friendly.
It was good--thanks for making books affordable!
I love the website, it's easy and convenient!

Thank you for the wide variety of literature choices for the students. I like the way you can order from many catalogs at the same time. An added bonus for 2 of my students was finding an on-line order for their favorite book series, The Bad Guys.
Great selection of books. Online order process is quick and easy!
Happy with this site this year.
My kids always look forward to our book order.
Love this site, wish there was more stationary items too, love all the books though!!
It was very simple to place my order.
I have a coupon at school to get $10 to spend so I will wait to place the order.
What I wanted done, got done. I have any higher praise
I appreciate the opportunity for free/ cheap books for teachers.
Ease of use and books were aviailable
great site and easy to use!

I encourage the parents to purchase books through Scholastic.  They won't find a better deal anywhere else.  I am discouraged by how few students actually submit an order.   :-(    I use both the paper and digital format in order to reach the parents.
Very convenient, I love buying books for my child that we both can enjoy
Used this online bookclub for years!! love!!!
Trying to navigate the site and edit letters is very un-user friendly.

Very easy to order, even for my own child in 3rd grade, which I added to my order here as well. It was easy for me to use some of my points to add to my order and get books for the end of the year. It is easy to order with checks as parents send in requests. Some parents order online but not many.
Love the email reminders that a student order has been entered  Thank you
Scholastic's allows me to provide my students with a book a month that doesn't break the bank!
Lots of free books for my class due to their orders. thank you so much
The site was very easy to navigate. I had no problems. Love the wish list option. It makes it easier to decide which books to get right away and which ones you can wait on.
Actually, enjoy ordering books on your website.
Thank you for the $5 free book.
It is SOOOOOOOO  much better than the last couple of years.  YAY!!!
I've had problems with shipping the past two years and the incentives have not been very good so I have not placed many orders this year.
I love the option of shipping to their teacher or to home.  Always great prices with great quality!
It was a great website to navigate.
Love that I can order securely
Easy and affordable and able to support our teacher’s class library.
East, quick, convenient and great deals!
Like that I can order books as gifts & my Grandchildren's classes benefit.
I love ordering books from here!!! There’s always a great selection
Much easier to use than before!
This makes ordering scholastic books so simple and enjoyable
I think the site is pretty user friendly.
Great books, I was able to apply a coupon.  Easy to find the books. I feel books are a little expensive.
freezes at this point and I can't move forward

What I really, really, like about Scholastic Book Clubs is that they sometimes give you the opportunity to get a $5 book for free with a special code or coupon which makes their website different from any other website that sells books. That is why I have rated Scholastic Book Clubs "Very Good".                                                            Sincerely,                                                                                  Giana Cigliano
Love scholastics books!   They have great books.  The children love to order
I've always supported Scholastic Book clubs, although we didn't have online ordering at the time!
No place to add money to account for him to use at the book fair. Cannot locate the book fair that starts tomorrow. A poor site is an understatement.
I am a librarian and parent. Love the site.
Easy to find exactly what I needed to do!
Easy to navigate and my order is always correct.  Love Scholastic!
I love the prices and the website is so easy to use.
I am a grandma and live 3 states away from my grandson. I love that I am able to order for him via online and have the books delivered to his classroom!

The website was very easy to navigate and place my order.  Very pleased with the items available for purchase.. so many things to choose from in making my child's reading journey fun!  Love the site and will be back in the future
I absolutely LOVE Scholastic Book Clubs!!! I have really enjoyed the book selections this year.  Thank you for providing this service to children in America!
Your site is very easy to navigate.  I am extremely happy with Scholastic Book Club!!
having problems navigating the site I'll keep working at it.

I have 5 school age grandchildren who like to read 'their own books,' as well as library books.  It is important to 'grow readers' and I will do what I can to promote reading whenever I can.  Thank you for your WONDERFUL commitment to education: parents, teachers, children and caring adults.   Sincerely,  a retired teacher, lifelong learner, compassionate member of the human race
Love the reward program. Best reward program out there!

I have ordered from Scholastic books for many years.  I am concluding my teaching career at the end of this school year.  I have purchased many books for my classroom library, for my students, and for myself and my family.  I always encourage new teachers to join.
Always a quick and easy process
I am happy to be able to purchase an item for my class.
it was really easy to use and they have a huge variety of books and stories for a grades including pre
Thanks!  Love your books and website.

I get emails from scholastic and I had a code for 15% of and it would not work. I just received the email yesterday so I know it is not expired. I was a little up set that I could not use the 15% off today.
It's hard to locate the bonus catalog.
I'd like to see more $1.00 books every month and sets of grafe level summer activity books.

Every click on the checkout page kept bringing me to this survey. Then I’d have to go back to the tab on my iPad to get to the checkout. If I hadn’t been paying attention, I would not have gone back to the checkout page to hit submit. I would have thought my order was done, when it would not have beenone unhappy second grader!
Just difficult to navigate on a phone

My child has a book fair at school and I want to connect to it so that the school will get credit for what I order and he would get the buy one get one special. But I won't order if I cant  I don't like to send cash with him.
was logged out when i tried to go back to finish transaction.
The selection of books has improved. Earlier in the school year there was not a lot of good books to pick from.

For a new teacher, this was a difficult site to navigate. It took forever for me to figure out how to get flyers for my students to take home to parents. Many of my parents aren't interested in digital flyers.  Also, I teach special education and most of my students are not reading on grade level so sending home flyers that say kindergarten or 1st grade is a little off-putting to parents of 4th and 5th graders. maybe leave that off the flyer that goes home. Or modify it somehow.  I also teach a range of grades which is complicated when selecting how many students I have. I understand that most of your clientele is full classrooms of 25-30 students, but I end up with an excess of left over flyers. Not sure if the trees can be saved or if money can be saved by not having to send out so many. If not, then oh well.

I was confused about when and how I could use the coupon I earned.  It took me awhile to figure out that it could be used towards NEXT month's order.      On another note, the reason why I didn't have my class order was because I was waiting for the May catalogues.  I haven't received it yet and at this point it will be too late.  I would really love getting the monthly catalogues earlier for example, the May catalogues by the middle of April or December catalogues by mid November.

I was confused about when and how I could use the coupon I earned.  It took me awhile to figure out that it could be used towards NEXT month's order.      On another note, the reason why I didn't have my class order was because I was waiting for the May catalogues.  I haven't received it yet and at this point it will be too late.  I would really love getting the monthly catalogues earlier for example, the May catalogues by the middle of April or December catalogues by mid November.
I appreciate the bonus points so that I can continue to build my classroom library.

One of my student's online order was deleted. I had to reach out to the parent to reorder all the  items because the order disappeared. Your website has always been very difficult and confusing to navigate, unfortunately, so I'm not sure if in trying to navigate it, I deleted the order accidently because the parent got a message saying that "the teacher" deleted the order. It was very frustrating.
Can we make this more like a "natural" and responsive site? This site did not seem to work as expected... and sometimes, not work.
It told me I could not order some of my books. Not enough available. I was disappointed.
The offerings as of late have been disappointing.  Very few for early childhood (1-3 years) and the books have gotten too pricy.  As such, we have less interest from our families.
The offerings as of late have been disappointing.  Very few for early childhood (1-3 years) and the books have gotten too pricy.  As such, we have less interest from our families.

I wish you would link all our earned coupons to our account so we wouldn't have to keep track of them and try to remember to use them.  If you are going to offer extra bonus points or free book picks it would be awesome if they automatically showed in our account like our bonus points do.
Hard to find all that's available on mobile format

My problem is that I will now have two $10 to use in May. However, this is my last book order for the year. I set up my book order early to give families time to order, and have it before the end of the school year.

I wish I could search by price or item type.  Sometimes I may search puzzles or decodable books, etc. and although it is in the title of the item, the item does not come up.  It seems like a glitch in the search.  Overall, I think the site is easy and user friendly.  I love to search for learning materials, not just books.  I wish there were more in the fliers.  The students often want the puzzles, games, etc. that I have purchased from Scholastic over the years.  I wish you also still had big books.  Thank you for the great site!
Wish there were some good books for parents too.

I found the rewards pretty ridiculous.  A teacher who had a class order of $25 dollars would get the same amount of money to spend as me, a teacher who had a $200+ order.  I also hate that Scholastic doesn't allow you to spend the rewards in that order. Scholastic has become very disappointing.

The site is not always user friendly.  When searching for book titles, it often does not come up with the right book.  The site does not direct you to spend your free money.  If you didn't know, you would loose it.
In the boxed sets, I would like to see each book individually

It’s so confusing trying to remember which options to choose - book club, parent, etc to place an order. I kept entering the code for the book on the flyer and it wouldn’t come up. I was scrambling all over the website to try to figure out what I needed to click to access my kids’ school profiles to order. Confusing.
It would be great if customers received notification that their order was received.
Well, my bonus points coupons were expired....bummer
I wish there were more bilingual book options available.
There needs to be a sale/clearance section.
I don't like the website format. Just show me everything available and let me filter it.
I have found other books outside the club and for some reason i cant locate these book bundles or other books i want from Scholastic outside the book club. Very frustrating.
One of the books I wanted was out of stock and it was going to be my free book.
It froze up a couple times.
It's sometimes hard to find books based on reading level. We like to use levels based on I Can Read Books or the Steps. It'd be nice to filter that.
Did not accept my class code.
I can't seem to find the book I'm looking for although it was advertised on the homepage of Scholastic.
I am disappointed with the number of books that are inappropriate for elementary children.
It was very unclear how to enter my students order.
I wish there were more sales for teachers
Very hard to search categorically / hard to just browse

I like the ability to preview books for selection with a promo code, though I'd prefer if I could click on the title and open it in a new tab. Currently I can only see the preview, and in order to read more about the book, I have to exit the order/selection screen, browse for books, decide, go back to the cart, re-enter the promo code, browse again... and repeat.
This survey came up before I was finished ordering.
One of the books from the code on my flyer - Easter Bunny vs Tooth Fairy, when I added it it actually added a different book.  No problem, I found it!

I have loved Scholastic Books since I was a child, and have always ordered from you since I have become a teacher, but as a Christian educator, I was disappointed today to see that you have so many LGBTQ books. I don't like having to look through my order to make sure there are no references to this for my preschool children.
No problem, but I often have trouble easily switching between my teacher and parent accounts and I have to google how to do that every time.
I have a $250 gift card and will continue to shop until I find enough books have that value.

I wish $1 books would come back along with the option to find $1 books
I don’t know if I properly submitted the order because I was redirected here and have no confirmation email.
I wish there was an option to purchase a book for the class. If there is one i cant find it
I wish my code for bonus points would be emailed to me.
Not today, but last Friday when I submitted my order.  Also, tried to call on phone today and was on hold for over twenty minutes.
I can't always find what I'm looking for.

It is always tricky to browse the site when I am looking for books for my magazine. I wish as a teacher there was a special view we had that didn't include the magazines to scroll though (I never have one left for me after passing them out to students). I would love a way to just view the whole selections of all available currently for students of the age I select or teach.
I was hoping to find a book for a student within her Lexile level. I don't see how to search by Lexile levels. I will keep looking. Thanks!
There were a lot of books that weren’t available, it would be helpful if it said it was unavailable before you clicked through.
I am still working on the order but will place soon
I needed 1 more copy of the Splat the Cat Oopsie Daisy book & couldn't find a way to order just one,
I was trying to find a certain book to apply for the free $5 with code READS and it wasn’t showing up. Maybe it was out of stock. I’m not sure why it wasn’t showing. (How to Catch the Tooth Fairy)
I was unable to check on an item and see when it will be delivered.
When you have coupons to use, it would be nice to search by price point instead of just grade level.

I will be switching grade levels next year and wanted to take a peek at 1st grade options for books.   Suggestion: It would be wonderful to have some sort of "Vintage" section where I could order books that are not the most recent ones that have come out. I was looking for Officer Buckle and Gloria and it isn't available here, so I'll have to look elsewhere.
Kept getting kicked to the home page when using back button.

I wish it was easier to purchase books for our whole classroom.  Most teachers order book sets for their students.  Having sets of affordable books would be SO helpful.  I feel like the selection for affordable class sets are getting less and less each year.

I wish it was easier to purchase books for our whole classroom.  Most teachers order book sets for their students.  Having sets of affordable books would be SO helpful.  I feel like the selection for affordable class sets are getting less and less each year.

With the free book option, if you are going to allow customers to choose from a limited selection of books, maybe have that open in a separate window, rather than a list where you have to click on the titles individually.

Once I entered my order I got an email with a code if I entered an order in April of 25+ I would get an extra 400 points. I was told in a email they would credit my account but i havent seen that credit yet.
went to the wrong scholastic site first
Would like to be able to add my whole preschool (I'm administrator) to email list. It is limited.
There are times when all I want to do is place an order and pop-ups come on and interfere with that process.
I went to the Flyers tab to open a flyer to look at it, but it wouldn't let me open it.  It would take me to a blank page.
I wish it sent me a reminder to order.  These have been sitting in the que  for a month

I tried to complete this order using my mobile phone, but user interactions and modals on the mobile experience do not resize themselves appropriately.  It was sometimes impossible to navigate because necessary button interactions couldn't be reached (were cut off) due to the design not being responsive.
I can not figure out an easy way to redeem my points.

It would be easier to enter sale codes and just have the price adjusted if the chosen book is already in the shopping cart.   It's an extra step to search for it again, then delete one previously added to the cart.
There's one website from the teacher and then we I log in it's showing up as another website and then I have to log in again. all in all I logged in 3 times.

I HATE the scholastic site.  It is difficult to navigate. Books are not always available.  The selection is horrid - eg having the 3rd book of a series but not 1st or 4th.  Overall - I used to support scholastic more but between the issues above and that the selection of parent and teacher sites do not match - I have INTENTIONALLY going to BN and Amazon instead of scholastic for 1/2 my orders and ONLY order from y’all for teachers.

I HATE the scholastic site.  It is difficult to navigate. Books are not always available.  The selection is horrid - eg having the 3rd book of a series but not 1st or 4th.  Overall - I used to support scholastic more but between the issues above and that the selection of parent and teacher sites do not match - I have INTENTIONALLY going to BN and Amazon instead of scholastic for 1/2 my orders and ONLY order from y’all for teachers.

I am waiting for my son to get home to open the box himself, but I wanted to get a preview of what i ordered (completely forgot what it was). Want him to have a great experience knowing something came in for him today.
i did have to reset password but that was easy and i was able to access my account.  I was looking for Elephant and Piggy books in a pack! and found them.   will submit my order at another time  thnx
Your sight is very difficult to navigate and find what you want when you don’t have a book title or code!

I was not thrilled to have to sort through so many books that are so 'woke' and liberal in nature.  I don't understand why you choose as a company to help propagate sexually immoral and socialist values.  While I did fine a few books that I thought would be a good fit for my child, I am choosing to not purchase from you because I am actively voting with my dollars and plan to purchase elseward.  You have made your choice as a business, I get to make mine as a consumer.
Extremely easier to order and receive the books this year!  Had many problems in the past.  Unfortunately the poor economy is a reflection in my low orders overall.

I just wish that there were more cheap books for me to purchase for my students.  I love to give books as gifts, but rarely ever find books that are in the $1-1.25 range.  I found ONE today and bought it!!
It didn’t show which  teacher I could choose. My son has 2 different teacher

Been doing this 28 years.  I dislike how you need to have larger orders now to get the $1 books. Schools that have families with money enough to get to that tier don't NEED the $1 books. Schools in low income districts could really use that more. Alas, the rich get richer in America.
I wanted to search by the reading level (GLR) and didn’t see an option to be able to do that.
books that are $2 no longer available but available for a higher price in a different search.  I'm sure this violates some sort of consumer protection for bait and switch.
On my profile I have entered that I have 80 students...I still only receive 1 packet of order forms.
I wish there were hard cover books as options from scholastic.

I love Scholastic! I think there are great options for books and the prices are very reasonable.   Two suggestions: One suggestion I have is having a lower grade level book and an upper grade level book for the $1 books each week. There was a lot of lower level books this year and my 4th graders were past that. I would have ordered more books if there were more 4th grade level book options.   Second suggestion: the $1 books that were picked this year for the upper grades did not align with their interests. A lot of the books are classics but do not seem interesting to them so we didn't order.
Trying to order books off the flyer was very difficult. There should be a way to just click an "I have a flyer" button from the home page!

As a teacher, we help market your company to our students and we do all of the sales. The points earned are not nearly enough from a $500 + sale every time I enter a book club order. This makes me less likely to promote this book club to our students.
I got on to order but had a visitor in class and parent call so I will finish later

I am frustrated that you did the auto-ship on an order. I had a family submit an order after the deadline last month. I was holding off on the next order until the end of the month. The family knew and agreed. Then you auto-shipped it and I didn't get to add the total into my monthly order to earn free books. I spent my own money to get the total up to 25 to use my coupon and free shipping. However, if you hadn't auto-shipped it would have worked out great. You should ask permission from the teacher to do this.

I do not like the way the $10 free books are set up. I have not used any at all this year because of the extra step to keep track of a silly code. This is one of the worst ideas you have had. I've been ordering books for over 30 years. I'm about ready to be done with future orders.

I love being able to order books for my grand daughter and have them sent to her teacher.I do have a little bit of a problem.I have trouble remembering what I've previously bought for her.I there a way I can look up a book to see if i've bought it already??
My students bought books but gave me cash. The delivery fee and tax are on me?

I rated a 7 because I feel like with everything else in this world prices have gone up. I remember when majority of the books were $5 or under. Also, I get charged for tax every time for years and we are a 501c3 non profit organization.

I rated a 7 because I feel like with everything else in this world prices have gone up. I remember when majority of the books were $5 or under. Also, I get charged for tax every time for years and we are a 501c3 non profit organization.
3 of the books or book sets that students wanted are out of stock.  I did not know the Spring Gift Books Order form would be expired so early.  I may just return their money.
My order was automatically submitted and NOW I have to figure out how to get my free books.  This is the DUMBEST thing you have ever done!!!  Just so mad at it all.

I was surprised to see a student order that was placed on 4/30 automatically submitted before my due date.  I currently do not have enough orders for free shipping for my own classroom order.  Not sure I will have enough by my due date to not have to pay for shipping for my own order.
I can't register an account.  There are so many console errors.
I appreciate that my order was automatically submitted, but is it too late to go back and get my free book picks and place a teacher order?

I'm disappointed that it automatically submitted my order.  Since it submitted automatically, I was not able to redeem my coupons and bonuses, or place my own order.  It has never done this before.  This is so sad.  I'm highly disappointed.

I had a student order that was processed before I submitted it. I was planning on adding my teacher order as well and now I cannot order what I wanted without having to pay shipping. This has never happened before.
I can't find my customer number.
I could not find Peak by Roland Smith
It has been a few years since I have signed in to Scholastic to order books. I noticed that all of the points I had accumulated at one point have disappeared.  Is there anyway I can get them back?
My class on-line orders were done automatically.  I don't know why this happened.  I was unable to enter my class orders that were not on-line orders.
The system does not alert you about a book that is in your cart that was previously ordered. Please consider adding that feature.
I couldn't order the item #s  until I realized I had to shop froma specific class page.

Can’t find all the books on scholastic.com

I wasn't able to choose the 5th grade teacher.
I couldn't find a variety of Junie B Jones books in Spanish. I wanted to purchase Junie B Jones. Tengo un Pio pio en el bolsillo

I had ordered these items back in February, but I guess because I messed up the timing or something, the order was cancelled but I didn't get a message about that...finally followed up this week and discovered what had happened. This time I'm ordering on the same day I got the email about ordering from my child's teacher, so hopefully it goes through this time!

Do not like the new automatic submittion of orders at the end of the month. I had out my slips and give a due date for the class. Now half my order will be coming before the whole class gets to order.

I dislike the auto order that just started!  With my April due date being 5/2, it ordered part of my order and then I did not get my full rewards. So I had to chat with someone to deal with this!   I am not happy about this feature.
I couldn't find my daughters teacher initially, but once I logged into my account I was able to order to her classroom. Not sure why that might've been but I was able to complete my order after all!
One of the books was out of stock but a parent sent in a check. I am not sure what to do.
The site is harder to navigate than it was before the pandemic.
I get annoyed with the pop up for offers.  but then am asked to put in an offer code.  can't this be streamlined somehow?
A book is out of stock and i couldn't place that but Sheila was very helpful.
A book listed in the handouts was not on the website.
2 books sets were no longer available.  And I have never found the $1 selection.
I had an order in my cart waiting for my order date and it was all deleted .
My credit card from my google account wouldn't load and I had to enter the CC manually.
Wish u had more books in stock
Alot not in stock from flyer sent home
For some reason, my order was submitted.  I did not submit it.

Using  the mobile version to open an account, the page emptied my information when I clicked submit, and prompted me to complete it again. On the third attempt I decided to close that page and log in from what appeared to be the home page, which is how I learned my information had indeed been successfully submitted.
I am disappointed in the summer reading book selection/prices.
I am disappointed in the summer reading book selection/prices.
couldn't find any preschool mother's day books
When I placed my order, my payment transaction froze.
